records.addlTxt:
Defendant Dennis R Leggett in court with attorney Douglas J. Rebholz.  Brittany Skye Kachingwe appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Deputy Court Clerk: KAR.
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.

AS TO COUNT 1: The Court ordered defendant to serve 5 days in the House of Correction, consecutive to Count 3 and any other sentence, with credit for 0 (zero) days time served. The Court granted Huber privileges, pursuant to 303.08 Wis. Stats. for work and treatment. Court ordered defendant to pay $100.00 plus all applicable court costs and fees by 9/8/16, or to be docketed as a civil judgment, cash bail to apply.

AS TO COUNT 3: Court ordered defendant to serve 50 days in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence with credit for 2 days time served.  Huber privileges for work and treatment ONLY.  Court STAYED the sentence to 9/11/15 at 5:00 pm.  Court ordered defendant to pay a fine of $350.00 plus all mandatory costs, penalties, surcharges, and $50.00 ignition interlock surcharge by 9/8/16, cash bail to apply. Non-payment will result in the entry of a civil judgment.  Court ordered AODA assessment and Driver's Safety Plan.  Defendant to cooperate with any treatment recommended.  Court ordered defendant's driving privileges revoked for a period of 12 months.  Court orders defendant restricted to operation of vehicles equipped with an ignition interlock device for 12 months to commence upon eligibility to reinstate license. 

Filed;
- Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
- Pretrial Incarceration Credit;
- Sentening Referral Form;
- Driver Assessment and Driver's Safety Plan.
